Examples for WebService::OCI
============================

These scripts use the DEFAULT profile from ~/.oci/config unless noted.
See WebService::OCI::Guide to set that up, and WebService::OCI::Cookbook for
more recipes. Run each with no/invalid arguments to see its usage.

Getting started
  first-call.pl                 print your Object Storage namespace (hello world)
  whoami.pl                     show the authenticated user and tenancy (Identity)
  raw-request.pl METHOD SERVICE PATH [k=v ...]
                                a minimal generic caller

Discovery
  discover.pl --compartment OCID [--shape NAME] [--os "Oracle Linux"]
                                availability domains, shapes per AD, recent images
  list-compartments.pl [--compartment OCID]
                                walk the compartment subtree (find OCIDs)

Compute
  list-instances.pl <compartment-ocid> [profile]
                                list instances, following pagination
  launch-instance.pl --compartment OCID --subnet OCID --ssh-key FILE [...]
                                launch an instance end to end (--retry rides out
                                capacity/429/5xx)
  instance-action.pl --instance OCID --action START|STOP|RESET|... [--wait]
                                start/stop/reset an instance
  parallel.pl --compartment OCID [--concurrency 8]
                                fan out per-instance lookups concurrently (fork;
                                one client per worker)
  teardown.pl --compartment OCID [--instance OCID] [--vcn OCID]
                                terminate an instance and/or delete a VCN

Networking
  setup-network.pl --compartment OCID [--name demo]
                                create a VCN + internet gateway + public subnet
  security-rule.pl --security-list OCID --port N [--source CIDR]
                                open a port (read-modify-write with if-match)

Object Storage
  objectstorage.pl <compartment-ocid> <bucket> [file]
                                namespace + list buckets; optional up/download
  object-sync.pl --bucket NAME --dir PATH [--prefix STR]
                                upload a directory (skip objects already present)
  object-pull.pl --bucket NAME --dir PATH [--prefix STR]
                                download a bucket into a directory
  presigned-url.pl --bucket NAME --object KEY [--days 7]
                                create a pre-authenticated request (shareable URL)
  multipart-upload.pl --bucket NAME --file PATH [--part-mb 128]
                                upload a large file in parts

Other services
  secret.pl --secret OCID [--out FILE]
                                fetch a Vault secret bundle (uses base_url for the
                                secrets.vaults.<region>.oci.oraclecloud.com host)
  metrics.pl --compartment OCID [--query 'CpuUtilization[1m].mean()']
                                query the Monitoring service (MQL)

For the command-line tool, see: oci-rest --help
